				<p>Without the map, the state space is just what the robot can sense from its immediate position.  So to a certain extent, the map is just a way to "look ahead".  The learned behavior in the map-less scenario will be essentially "do the same thing as before but go slower because we don't know where the turns are this time".  (Presumably, you'll be able to tell where the edges of the track are.)</p>
